[4] Cholera - Nigeria (Bauchi State)
Date: Wed, 26 Oct 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: The Daily Independent [edited]
<http://www.independentng.com/news/nnoct260509.htm>

3 people have been confirmed dead and several others are critically ill at
the Bayara General Hospital following the outbreak of cholera in Bayara, a
suburb in Bauchi Local Government in the state capital. The sickness,
characterized by vomiting and diarrhea, has affected the community due to
lack of potable water in the area. Rain water is the major source of water
despite the proximity to the state capital.
The source of drinking water is a stream which usually dries up during the
dry season.
[Byline: Godwin Egbara]
